	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_32871070"><p>Deflation did <i>not</i> "work out quite well."  It absolutely sucked for farmers (which, when we had deflation, was basically everyone.)  You had to take out a bank loan to purchase seed up front; you would pay your loan back with interest after harvest.</p><p>Deflation makes those loans a raw deal - you might pay $1200 on a $1000 loan, but each of those dollars is worth more after a growing season's worth of deflation.  Because of deflation, you pay the bank much more in constant dollars.</p><p>I'm also not sure why massive d<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

