		<div id="comment_body_32869944"><p>
It doesn't matter what you can use it for, so long as it is a FINITE resource and isn't easily replicated.  Gold costs labour and resources to extract.  The government can't just whip up a million ounces out of thin air to inflate their currency with.  That gold is a result of human labour and resources spent.  Fiat (paper, electronic, non backed) money can easily be replicated for far less than the labour quantity required than the goods/services it can purchase.  It is thus liable to abuse by a governmen<span class="substr"> </span></p></div>
	</div>

